dict.string: Molino Canyon: Geo History The Gneiss rock: What is it? Pronounced "nice". It's the main grey colored rock. - What are the white lines you see on them? Quartz veins, with feldspar in there too.

- How was it formed? It is a metamorphic rock. It started off as granite and then under lots of heat and pressure (inside the earth/under the earthâ€™s surface) got squashed/metamorphosed into gneiss. See the lineation of minerals? - If you see one, take note of the color and size of each individual mineral/ grain, you can compare that with rock units further up the mountain, namingly at Stop 3: Windy Point.
